        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 6:13PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 613 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Palo Pinto, or 13 miles southwest of Mineral Wells, moving west
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lake Palo Pinto around 620 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Santo and Lone Camp.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
